This study aims to establish when, and under what circumstances, IRF performs well in terms of its use and the query modification terms selected as a result of its use.
In this paper we present a study into the use and effectiveness of IRF in an online search environment.
In this paper we use data derived from that experiment to study factors affecting the utility of IRF. 
As the quality of the query submitted to the system directly affects the quality of search results , the issue of how to improve search queries has been studied extensively in IR research 